      <hedline>
        <hl1>Oil Isn't Reason Enough for War</hl1>
      </hedline>
      <abstract>
        <p>Feroze Sidhwa letter on Thomas L Friedman's Jan 5 Op-Ed; holds energy conservation and climate change are not what average Arab is concerned with; holds what Arabs want is end to Israeli occupation of West Bank and Gaza, and for West, especially United States, to stop interfering in internal affairs of Arab countries</p>
      </abstract>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>To the Editor:</p>
        <p>Re ''A War for Oil?,'' by Thomas L. Friedman (column, Jan. 5):</p>
        <p>''Energy conservation'' and ''climate change'' are not what the average Arab is concerned with. What Arabs want is an end to the Israeli occupation of the West Bank and Gaza, and for the West, especially the United States, to stop interfering in the internal affairs of Arab countries.</p>
      </block>
      <block class="full_text">
        <p>To the Editor:</p>
        <p>Re ''A War for Oil?,'' by Thomas L. Friedman (column, Jan. 5):</p>
        <p>''Energy conservation'' and ''climate change'' are not what the average Arab is concerned with. What Arabs want is an end to the Israeli occupation of the West Bank and Gaza, and for the West, especially the United States, to stop interfering in the internal affairs of Arab countries.</p>
        <p>Mr. Friedman is concerned about the environment, but the average Middle Easterner has more immediate problems to worry about.</p>
        <p>FEROZE SIDHWA  Baltimore, Jan. 5, 2003</p>
      </block>
